    "is_good_patch": true,
    "synth_pr": "\n## Title: Fix cross-layer parameter mismatch in NR UE Capability Enquiry generation\n\n### Summary\nThere is a cross-layer parameter mismatch between PHY, MAC, and RRC causing inconsistent operation downstream of function rrc_eNB_generate_NR_UECapabilityEnquiry. The function accesses nr_gnb_freq_band[0][0] without checking if any gNB cells are configured, which can lead to accessing uninitialized memory or invalid data.\n\nThis fix adds proper validation before accessing the band information arrays.\n\n### Changes\n- `openair2/RRC/LTE/rrc_eNB.c`: Added checks in rrc_eNB_generate_NR_UECapabilityEnquiry to verify gNB cell configuration before accessing nr_gnb_freq_band\n- `openair2/RRC/LTE/rrc_eNB.c`: Added similar validation in rrc_eNB_generate_UECapabilityEnquiry with graceful fallback\n\n### Reproduction\nUnder certain network configurations where no gNB cells are properly initialized, calling rrc_eNB_generate_NR_UECapabilityEnquiry results in segmentation fault or invalid memory access. The issue manifests when:\n1. No gNB cells are configured (num_gnb_cells == 0)\n2. The function attempts to access nr_gnb_freq_band[0][0] \n3. Uninitialized memory is read, causing undefined behavior\n\nSymptoms include RRC connection failures and eNB crash during UE capability negotiation phase.\n"
}